# Help: Software RAID (MD) layers
#
# MD RAID is used by fstests and blktests setups that need
# multi-disk arrays. MD is the bool umbrella covering the entire
# drivers/md menu (software RAID and Device Mapper); BLK_DEV_MD is
# the tristate "RAID support" driver that provides the /dev/md*
# devices. MD_BITMAP (default y) is set explicitly so merge_config
# does not miss it.
#
# MD_RAID456 selects RAID6_PQ, ASYNC_MEMCPY, ASYNC_XOR, ASYNC_PQ,
# and ASYNC_RAID6_RECOV through Kconfig select, so they do not
# need to appear here.
#
# MD_AUTODETECT depends on BLK_DEV_MD=y and therefore lives in the
# builtin/ counterpart, where the whole chain is promoted.
# See: drivers/md/Kconfig
# See: https://docs.kernel.org/admin-guide/md.html
# See: https://raid.wiki.kernel.org/

CONFIG_MD=y
CONFIG_BLK_DEV_MD=m
CONFIG_MD_BITMAP=y
CONFIG_MD_LINEAR=m
CONFIG_MD_RAID0=m
CONFIG_MD_RAID1=m
CONFIG_MD_RAID10=m
CONFIG_MD_RAID456=m
